@mallochine - SteveL said "for now" but it's just to be clear: this isn't really just "for now" -- if you want to write cmdlets that target _PowerShell Core_, you can't use features that aren't in netstandard2.0. In fact, you must compile targeting .NET Standard 2.0

Additionally, any Windows machines will need at least .NET Framework 4.6.1 (and possibly 4.7, depending on features you use) if you want to be sure the module will work in full desktop "Windows PowerShell" ...

You _can_ cross-compile (producing separate assemblies targeting each framework), but your code still has to compile against .NET Standard 2.0 to work in PowerShell Core.
